<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861203-0114 </DOCNO><HL> Bindley Intends to AcquirePharmaceutical Company</HL><DD> 12/03/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BINDTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> INDIANAPOLIS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bindley Western Industries Inc. said it signed a letter of intent to acquire Osman Drug Group, a Stamford, Conn.-based wholesale distributor of pharmaceuticals and health and beauty aids.    Terms weren't disclosed.    Bindley, a drug wholesale concern, said closely held Osman, which had annual sales of more than $160 million for its fiscal year ended June 30, consists of Stamford Superior Drug Co. and Special Services Inc., both of Stamford, and New England Wholesale Drug Co., of Dorchester, Mass.    Bindley said the letter of intent contemplates that Bindley would acquire for cash all of the shares outstanding of the companies owned by Osman. The acquisition is subject to several conditions, including negotiation of a definitive agreement and a closing on or before Dec. 31. </TEXT></DOC>